The paper proposes a new approach for network embedding using non-Markovian random walk, specifically variants of vertex-reinforced random walk (VRRW). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses experimental results on link prediction and node classification, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
